Designed for use on all AR-15 rifles equipped with a carbine style buffer tube. To install remove the factory pistol grip and replace it with the provided Interface Block. SSAR-15 replaces the factory adjustable stock by sliding onto the buffer tube. All tools required to install are provided. Shooter activates the firing mechanism by moving the upper assembly forward. When it comes time to choose your everyday carry gun there is a lot to consider. You need something that is reliable, accurate, and easy to wear all day. You need something that you can enjoy shooting a lot, because there is no substitute for practice. That's where the T3 comes in. We designed this pistol to be pleasing to the eye, but also to be a workhorse that can stand up to thousands and thousands of rounds.

The T3 has the best features for any gun its size. The frame is based on the Officer model, but for those with large hands, it features an extended magazine well that gives you the length you need to get all your fingers on the grip. Another consideration is weight. The T3 actually weighs one ounce lighter than most officer size 1911s. This makes the T3 the first choice for an all-day carry pistol.

Heinie Slant-Pro Straight Eights Night Sights are standard. The mainspring housing, as well as the rear of the slide, are horizontally serrated to match. This feature also helps prevent snags on silk lined jackets and coats that checkering often causes. The top of the slide is also serrated to reduce glare. A Nighthawk Custom© lightweight aluminum trigger that has been blacked-out using Perma Kote™ breaks between 3.5 and 4 lbs with no creep. When you put all of these features in one package, you come up with the finest carry gun you can own. All you add is practice.

title: For Sale/Trade:  MEC 650 12 Gauge Shotshell Reloader
postcontent:
A loaded shell with every pull of the handle!  
Getting into trap this year and need to load more shells?
If you have been loading with a single stage press and you need to do more volume, let me know. It's a huge improvement over loading with a 600jr.

It is not the one that automatically indexes (that's the 9000), but it's also not $600.  

It comes with 1 oz and 1 1/8 oz shot bars, as well as at least two powder bushings.  I will provide my (relatively) local source of additional powder bushings, etc.  Both bottles are present and serviceable.  They both have plastic plugs and metal caps. I "lost" the rubber gromet from the shot bottle after it came loose, fell into the shot partition of the bar and caused 150+ shells to be loaded with unacceptable crimps and 3/4 oz shot instead of 1 oz. The gromet was a redundancy anyway because the shot partition has a captive rubber insert to prevent shearing. The press performed flawlessly after that (aside from some operator headspace and timing issues) until I upgraded to The Beast.  I do have the spent primer cup that it didn't come with, but I ordered as a replacement part from MEC.  The wad guide set is present and doesn't have any broken fingers.

If you have questions, let me know and I will answer them.  I don't know everything, but I got pretty proficient with it and have upgraded to The Monster Ponsness Warren, so the 650 is excess.

This will make someone a fantastic press at a great price. Please get in touch with offers.  

Trap season is in full swing.  Everybody is probably feeling the pinch of paying full retail for commercial shells.  Save some money and at least load your practice ammo.    I can give some help on finding most of the needed supplies.  (I have powder and know where to get primers and wads at the best prices.  I also know where to get reclaimed shot.

If you need some supplies to get started, I can add them.  There would be an extra charge for this, but how much extra will be determined by how much of what items you need.  If it's powder you need, I have it listed.  If you're buying the press, I will come down from the prices of the Win AALite and Promo.

For sale is a Ruger LC9 the way it should be.  Gun has the RTK trigger installed by Galloway Precision with the Galloway trigger bar, hammer, and reduced power springs.  This is the 50% short stroke trigger system.  Reduces take up and over travel in the long DA only LC9.  These upgrades make it easier to be accurate with the first shot, and more accurate with follow up shots.    

Gun is also equipped with the Galloway stainless guide rod, and a set of XS Express Tritium Big Dot night sights.  All of these upgrades combine to make the LC9 an easy to shoot, safe, accurate carry pistol. 100% reliable with any ammo I could stuff in the magazine.  The gun has the magazine disconnect removed, (allows the weapon to be fired without a magazine inserted.  Highly desirable if the bad guy somehow hits your mag release and all you're left with is one in the chamber.) and the loaded chamber indicator mod done (why let the bad guy know if your gun is loaded or not?). 

Price is $450 FIRM with 3 Ruger mags and a finger extension, box and papers.  FTF only in Jax.  Must be 21 years of age, a FLORIDA RESIDENT, and sign a Bill of Sale.  Prefer CCW. title: For Sale:  Winchester 1400 - semi auto shotgun (12ga)
postcontent:
For sale is a 12 gauge semi-auto shotgun by Winchester. This is the Model 1400, which was manufactured under license to Sears Roebuck as the Model 300. In other words, the shotgun says Sears but it's a Winchester 1400 -- a quick Google search will confirm that this is a Winchester dressed in Sears clothing: http://tinyurl.com/omdkg58.  

The shotgun looks great and functions great. There is a *very* minor rust spot on the barrel, and the previous owner electro-penned a serial number onto the bottom of the trigger guard. Other than those minor blemishes, the wood and steel look great. I recently used this to shoot clays at Pintail Point and it functioned nicely. The only reason I'm selling is I've decided to consolidate things into 20ga.

title: For Sale:  Colt Collectors: 1960 Colt "Model 357" 6" near mint!
location: North Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
This is a 98%+  Colt "Model 357" and is extremely difficult to find in any condition as less than 15,000 were made between 1952 and 1961.  It is the first frame mounted firing pin Colt and was introduced as the top of the line .357 named simply as such.   Production started before and briefly co-existed with the Python.  The 6" seems much less common than the 4" - but I don't know the numbers.  As typical for the time, one inside grip panel has handwritten pencil numbers matching the serial number.  Slight cylinder turn line and bluing wear at muzzle, otherwise pristine condition.  Being over 50 years old and limited production, this is a must have for serious Colt collectors and prices will undoubtedly continue increasing. 

Minnesota d.l., Permit to Purchase and cash only.
